   MARKER-ASSISTED SELECTION; SPRING WHEAT; TRANSCRIPTOME ANALYSIS;
   DISEASE-RESISTANCE; DEFENSE RESPONSE; GRAMINEARUM; BARLEY
AB To better understand the contribution of the quantitative fusarium head blight (FHB) resistance locus, 2DL QTL from Wuhan-1, we have characterized two pairs of sister lines carrying either the 2DL QTL or no known QTLs. In wheat spikes, our visual and microscopic observations suggested that the 2DL QTL suppress fungal infection in inoculated spikelets and reduce spread from spikelets to rachis. Transcriptome profiling of infected spikelets showed changes in expression for 487 probe sets between the 2DL-carrying and the null lines. Of 27 transcripts selected for validation, eight candidate genes with similar expression profiles between the two pair of lines were identified. Crown Copyright (C) 2015 Published by Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.
