TI cDNA library construction from meristematic tissue of finger millet
   panicle
SO CYTOLOGY AND GENETICS
LA English
DT Article
DE finger millet; meristem; cDNA library; cDNA fragment sequencing
ID ELEUSINE-CORACANA L.; SITE-SPECIFIC RECOMBINATION; GENES; WHEAT
AB A protocol to obtain full-length cDNA using a SuperScriptA (R) Full-Length cDNA Library Construction Kit II (Invitrogen, United States) was developed, and a high quality cDNA library of meristem tissue of finger millet panicle (Eleusine coracana (L.) Gaertn) was constructed. The titer of the constructed cDNA library was 3.01 x 10(5) CFU/mL, the average length of the insert was approximately 1070 base pairs, and the average efficiency of insertion of cDNA fragments was 99.5%. The sequencing of randomly selected clones created cDNA library was carried out. The cDNA sequences of clones were identified by BLAST search. The cDNA library analysis and selective sequencing indicate good functionality and full size of cDNA inserts of the clones. The constructed cDNA library from meristematic tissue of finger millet panicle is a good and reliable source for isolation and identification of key genes of metabolism and development of meristem as well for creation of new genetic markers for genetic research and molecular selection.
