TI The genetics of resistance to powdery mildew in cultivated oats (Avena
   sativa L.): current status of major genes
SO JOURNAL OF APPLIED GENETICS
LA English
DT Article
DE Avena sativa; Powdery mildew resistance; Monosomic analysis; Gene
   nomenclature; Blumeria graminis avenae isolates
ID MONOSOMIC LINES; CHROMOSOMAL LOCATION; F.SP AVENAE; CV KANOTA;
   IDENTIFICATION; EUROPE; WHEAT; RUST; TRANSLOCATION; MARKERS
AB The genetics of resistance to powdery mildew caused by Blumeria graminis f. sp. avenae of four cultivated oats was studied using monosomic analysis. Cultivar 'Bruno' carries a gene (Pm6) that shows a recessive mode of inheritance and is located on chromosome 10D. Cultivar 'Jumbo' possesses a dominant resistance gene (Pm1) on chromosome 1C. In cultivar 'Rollo', in addition to the gene Pm3 on chromosome 17A, a second dominant resistance gene (Pm8) was identified and assigned to chromosome 4C. In breeding line APR 122, resistance was conditioned by a dominant resistance gene (Pm7) that was allocated to chromosome 13A. Genetic maps established for resistance genes Pm1, Pm6 and Pm7 employing amplified fragment length polymorphism (AFLP) markers indicated that these genes are independent of each other, supporting the results from monosomic analysis.
C1 [Hsam, Sai L. K.; Zeller, Friedrich J.] Tech Univ Munich, Div Plant Breeding & Appl Genet, D-85354 Freising Weihenstephan, Germany.
   [Mohler, Volker] Bavarian State Res Ctr Agr, Inst Crop Sci & Plant Breeding, D-85354 Freising Weihenstephan, Germany.
