TI A novel PCR-based marker for identifying Ns chromosomes in
   wheat-Psathyrostachys huashanica Keng derivative lines
SO SPANISH JOURNAL OF AGRICULTURAL RESEARCH
LA English
DT Article
DE addition lines; marker-assisted selection; repetitive sequences; RAPD;
   SCAR
ID STRIPE-RUST RESISTANCE; SCAR MARKERS; ASSISTED SELECTION; TRANSLOCATION
   LINE; EX KUO; GENE; RAPD; IDENTIFICATION; ELONGATUM; GENOME
AB Psathyrostachys huashanica Keng is an endangered species that is endemic to China, which provides an important gene pool for wheat improvement. We developed a quick and reliable PCR-based diagnostic assay to accurately and efficiently detect P. huashanica DNA sequences from introgression lines, which was based on a species-specific marker derived from genomic DNA. The 900-bp PCR-amplified band used as a P. huashanica-specific RAPD marker was tested with 21 different plant species and was converted into a sequence-characterized amplified region (SCAR) marker by cloning and sequencing the selected fragments (pHs11). This SCAR marker, which was designated as RHS-23, could clearly distinguish the presence of P. huashanica DNA repetitive sequences in wheat-P. huashanica derivative lines. The specificity of the marker was validated using 21 different plant species and a complete set of wheat-P. huashanica disomic addition lines (1Ns - 7Ns, 2n = 44 = 22II). This specific sequence targeted the Ns genome of P. huashanica and it was present in all the seven P. huashanica chromosomes. Therefore, this SCAR marker is specific for P. huashanica chromosomes and may be used in the identification of alien repetitive sequences in large gene pools. This diagnostic PCR assay for screening the target genetic material may play a key role in marker-assisted selective breeding programs .
C1 [Wang, J.; Lu, M.; Du, W. L.; Zhang, J.; Dong, X. Y.; Wu, J.; Zhao, J. X.; Yang, Q. H.; Chen, X. H.] Northwest A&F Univ, Coll Agron, Shaanxi Key Lab Genet Engn Planting Breeding, Yangling 712100, Shaanxi, Peoples R China.
