TI Registration of Near-Isogenic Spring Wheat Germplasm with All
   Combinations of Homozygous R-Locus Genotypes
SO JOURNAL OF PLANT REGISTRATIONS
LA English
DT Article
ID SEED-COAT COLOR; GRAIN COLOR; GENES; LINES
AB Montana State University announces the release of two sets of near-isogenic lines of wheat (Triticum aestivum L.) containing all homozygous combinations of alleles at the R loci for seed color to provide materials for dissecting the impact of allelic variation at individual loci. Marker-assisted selection was used to develop all possible homozygous genotypes at the BC 5 generation after introducing alleles for white seed into lines homozygous for alleles causing red seed. The following sets of lines were developed, where the letter a indicates homozygosity for the a allele for white seed color and the letter b indicates homozygosity for the b allele for red seed color at R-A1, R-B1, and R-D1, respectively. Near-isogenic derivatives of 'Choteau' include JS16 (aaa) (Reg. No. GP-951, PI 665699), JS2 (abb) (Reg. No. GP-953, PI 665701), JS15 (aab) (Reg. No. GP-950, PI 665698), JS18 (aba) (Reg. No. GP-952, PI 665700), JS5 (baa) (Reg. No. GP-963, PI 665711), JS28 (bba) (Reg. No. GP-954, PI 665702), JS13 (bab) (Reg. No. GP-948, PI 665696), and JS14 (bbb) (Reg. No. GP-949, PI 665697). Near-isogenic derivatives of 'Vida' include JS37 (aaa) (Reg. No. GP-960, PI 665708), JS36 (abb) (Reg. No. GP-959, PI 665707), JS35 (aab) (Reg. No. GP-958, PI 665706), JS32 (aba) (Reg. No. GP-955, PI 665703), JS40 (baa) (Reg. No. GP-961, PI 665709), JS49 (bba) (Reg. No. GP-962, PI 665710), JS33 (bab) (Reg. No. GP-956, PI 665704), and JS34 (bbb) (Reg. No. GP-957, PI 665705). These lines will be useful for determining the impact of allelic variation at specific R loci on seed-related traits in hard wheat.
